{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606211"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:09:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:09:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15910"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15910","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15910"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.32,0.43,0.05,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8601"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95137"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8601","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8601"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15910"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78104"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"16"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"212"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"5470"},{"type":"tags","id":"8381"},{"type":"tags","id":"11724"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20605"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32074"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32075"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32628"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/95137"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic interested in participating in clinical research. She has read about a new medication being developed for migraine prophylaxis. She has a medical history of frequent migraines and takes sumatriptan as needed. She does not take any other regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical trial she is interested in aims to determine the optimal dose of the new medication and assess its effectiveness in treating migraines in 100 patients over six months. The medication has already been shown to be safe in healthy volunteers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the phase of this clinical trial?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Phase IV","Phase III","Phase II","Pilot study","Phase I"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis scenario describes a \u003Cstrong\u003EPhase II\u003C/strong\u003E clinical trial. Phase II trials typically involve 100-300 patients with the target condition and aim to establish the optimal therapeutic dose and provide preliminary evidence of efficacy. These trials follow successful Phase I safety studies but precede larger Phase III trials.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhase I\u003C/strong\u003E trials are first-in-human studies that primarily assess safety and tolerability. They typically involve 20-100 healthy volunteers (rather than patients with the condition) and focus on understanding the drug\u0027s pharmacokinetics and side effects. The stem indicates this phase has already been completed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhase III\u003C/strong\u003E trials are larger studies involving hundreds to thousands of patients across multiple centres. They compare the new treatment to existing standard therapy or placebo to definitively establish efficacy. The relatively small sample size (100 patients) and focus on dosing in this scenario is not consistent with a Phase III trial.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhase IV\u003C/strong\u003E trials occur after a drug has been approved and is in clinical use. They monitor long-term safety and effectiveness in the general population and may identify rare side effects or new indications. This medication is still in development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epilot study\u003C/strong\u003E is a small-scale preliminary study conducted to evaluate feasibility, time, cost, adverse events, and effect size in order to predict an appropriate sample size and improve upon the study design prior to performance of a full-scale research project. Although the phrase \u0022pilot study\u0022 can be used fairly vaguely, and may sometimes be used to refer to a phase 1 trial, the described trial is too large and structured to be a pilot study.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Phase I clinical trials primarily assess safety and tolerability in healthy volunteers","Phase II trials evaluate efficacy and optimal dosing in a small group of patients with the target condition","Phase III trials compare the new intervention to standard treatment in a large patient population"],"references":["Umscheid CA, Margolis DJ, Grossman CE. Key concepts of clinical trials: a narrative review. Postgrad Med. 2011;123(5):194-204. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21904102/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78104"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15910"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78104"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-27T11:06:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-27T11:07:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8601"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95137"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"16","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/16"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udcca","name":"Biostatistics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":